data.description: This lovely 4 bedroom home near the end of a cul-de-sac is close to it's Dorchester 2 schools, the military base, medical center, shopping, parks and more! Entering the home from the covered porch into a foyer which warmly greets you and your guests. The downstairs is all LVP, has high ceilings and is open. It's the perfect entertaining setup! The large kitchen has a pantry, lots of countertops and a breakfast bar. The kitchen sink location also enables you to look out the window to the private,. fully fenced backyard which backs up to woods. The family room, dining area, sliding doors to the tranquil screen porch, half bath and large storage closet make up the rest of the downstairs. Along with the attached 2 car garage.Upstairs there are 3 good sized guest bedrooms, full bath, laundry room and an extra large primary suite. The suite has two walk in closets and a side balcony.  Plus plenty of room for a desk, vanity table, dressers, and more!  The bathroom has dual sinks in the vanity, garden tub and stand up shower.     The backyard oasis includes the well sized screen porch, patio off of the porch AND a lovely bonfire pit with pavers at the back of the yard.  All backed by the woods for complete privacy. The banana trees make you feel like you are in a tropical oasis!    This one should not be missed!    A $1,400 Lender Credit is available and will be applied towards the buyer's closing costs and pre-paids if the buyer chooses to use the seller's preferred lender. This credit is in addition to any negotiated seller concessions.
